node.text:
We had some surprise furry guests at our weekly manager meeting this morning thanks to Nina and Ashley from the Humane Society of Sonoma County! This was Pliny’s first time meeting kitties and he did great. One brave kitten wanted to check Pliny out up close, then quickly changed her mind! This all-girl litter of 4 is available for adoption at @humanesocietysoco on Hwy. 12, along with many other loving animals in search of new forever homes! 🐶😻This weeks’ online offerings now available on our website- kittens not included!

@plinypup

node.text: NHRA Top Fuel drag races are back at Sonoma Raceway July 23rd-25th!  We are excited to announce that our friend, 3-time Top Fuel Champion Antron Brown, will be stopping by the Windsor brewery with his car next Wednesday, July 21st! Swing by anytime after 4pm to say hi to Antron and the team and grab a beer with us. There should be some cool photo ops with the Matco dragster parked in front of the brewery, too! @antronbrowntf @shoeracing #nhra #sonomanats #rrbccrew

node.text:
Vinnie and I are brewing “RnD Batch #26” in the pilot brewery today to celebrate our 26th wedding anniversary! This batch number just happened to coincide with our special anniversary brew. The beer is an IPA utilizing a couple of new brewing techniques, 4 different malt varieties, and Azacca, Mosaic and Simcoe hops. It will be available on tap at both pubs in about 3 weeks!  This weeks’ online offerings are now available including fresh batches of Mind Circus Hazy IPA and Mosaic Stack, both of which are being canned today! Cheers! ❤️🍻#mindcircushazyipa #mosaicstackipa #plinytheelder #26yearsandcounting

node.text:
Vinnie and I are headed out of town early tomorrow for a few days of R & R for the first time in a year, so I’m posting a little early this week! Many of you are likely doing the same thing and possibly headed to Sonoma County. Both pubs are open normal hours all weekend. The Windsor pub will also be open from 11-4 on Monday (Beer Garden ‘til 8)! This weeks’ online offerings are now available for shipping next Tuesday including a fresh batch of Porter canned today!  Wishing everyone a fun and safe Holiday weekend! #plinytheelder #blindpigipa #rrporter #stspils #happy4thofjuly

node.text: Today our Santa Rosa pub brewer, Sean, brewed our version of the CCBA Brewers Collaboration beer! This beer is a collaborative effort which celebrates and benefits the CCBA, our state trade association that protects and supports craft brewers in California. I recently had the honor of serving on the CCBA Board for 9 years ,so this collaboration has a particularly special meaning to me! Participating breweries will brew a style of their choosing, then donate funds to the CCBA. Our CCBA Brewers Collaboration beer is a West Coast IPA made with of Idaho 7, Strata, Azacca and Elixir hops. It will be available in cans and on draft at the pubs late July! Find out more about this fun project and view the list of participating breweries here: https://bit.ly/3w78vfI  #CCBABrewersCollab @cacraftbrewers #rrbccrew #craftbeer

node.text:
To commemorate the recent passing of our friend and legendary San Diego bartender, Nate Soroko, we added a little something special to this week’s Blind Pig bottling run! Regardless what bar or brewery employed Nate, Blind Pig remained one of his favorite beers. These bottles, Happy Hops cans, STS cans, and Pliny are available at both pubs and online now for shipping next week. Also sending several pallets of this Pig bottling down to Stone in So Cal on Monday for distribution. Let’s all raise a glass of our favorite beer to Big Nate 🍻. @toroislander you will be missed! 
#blindpigipa #ripbignate #happyhops #plinytheelder #stspils

node.text: We enjoyed one last round @fallingrocktaphouse tonight poured by none other than the King himself! After 24 years, this iconic Denver beer bar will close its doors one last time this Sunday, June 27th. Thank you to Chris, Cheryl, and the entire FRTH team for so many great memories! 🍻❤️#craftbeer #blindpigipa #plinytheelder @monkscafephilly @lostabbey @eclipticbrewing @craftbeerbrew @beeradvocate

Excited for this super fresh batch of #happyhops ! #happinessinabottle #craftbeer

node.text:
Celebrating the first mask-free day in well over a year with our fully vaccinated Santa Rosa kitchen crew! I’m so grateful to see their smiling, happy faces again! Some of our employees may still choose to wear a mask, but as long as they are vaccinated it is no longer required by the state. Things are looking up! Beers are also back online for shipping next week as it is going to be much cooler. We are adding the Green Cell Foam insulation back to can shipping boxes from now on to help keep them cool during the Summer months. Happy Father’s Day weekend to all of you awesome Dads out there! #rrbccrew #plinytheelder #rrbcdads #dadsfavoritebeer

node.text: On Day 2 of our big “National Sales Meeting” Vinnie and I took the team to Korbel winery in Guerneville where it all began! Russian River Brewing Company opened in 1997 at  Korbel where Vinnie was hired as the brewer and sole employee. We are pictured in front of the original brewery building which now holds their IT department. The tile, floor drains, and piping for glycol are all that remain. We then enjoyed some cold RRBC brews among the majestic coast redwoods and vineyards! rrbccrew #apicaldominance #korbelchampagnecellars

node.text: We celebrated the reopening of California yesterday with our entire sales team (all 7 of them!) at the Downtown pub! Also ran into a couple of OG RRBC bartenders enjoying a couple of pints whom some of you may recognize from years past! We will be bringing barstools back to both pubs on June 28th when we expect to have enough staff to accommodate additional seating. In the meantime, we are happy to see smiling happy faces again! #rrbccrew #rrbcsantarosa #mamamiapizza #pizzaandpliny
